<box> \begin{equation*}
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n {x_i}}{n}
\end{equation*}

Here, $\sum_{i=1}^n {x_i}$ represents the sum of the ages of each turtle, and $n$ is the total number of turtles. Given that 2 Ninja Turtles are 15 years old and the other 2 are 17 years old, the average age would be calculated as:

\begin{equation*}
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{(2*15) + (2*17)}{4} = \frac{30 + 34}{4} = \boxed{\frac{64}{4} = 16}.
\end{equation*}

Thus, the average age of the Ninja Turtles is 16 years.

